          <title>Ardour 8.12 released</title>
          <dc:creator><![CDATA[Paul Davis]]></dc:creator>
          <category>Blog</category>
          <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Ardour 8.12 is now available.</p>
<p>This is a hot-fix release, intended to fix two issues.</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>the bug fix introduced in 8.11 turned out to be incorrect, and broke several other things in subtle ways. 8.12 is a completely new approach to fixing the problem with region lengths after certain operations could cause sessions to be unloadable.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>for several previous versions, the packaging of translation files on macOS was broken. This has been corrected, and translations should work again on that platform.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p>Note that 8.12 will also correctly load sessions suffering from the problem referred to in <span class="hashtag">#1</span> above.</p>
<p>All users of earlier 8.x versions should plan to upgrade as soon as possible. Apologies for the problems the bug in <span class="hashtag">#1</span> has caused people - we hope this is a permanent, correct fix this time.</p>
<p>
